   [trans_dot.gif] [trans_dot.gif] [trans_dot.gif]
   California Lawmakers Reconvene Legislative Session
   [trans_dot.gif] [trans_dot.gif] [trans_dot.gif]

   [gov.ca.senate.democrats.gen.publicGetBlob?table=LIVE_STORY_IMAGES&main
   ID=156&subID=2] [trans_dot.gif] A Special Legislative Session has been
   called to address California's $12.5 million dollar budget deficit.
   [trans_dot.gif]
   [trans_dot.gif]
   California Lawmakers returned to Sacramento in January to complete work
   on the 2001-2002 legislative session. Faced with a looming budget
   deficit and fears of terrorism, Senators and Assembly members must work
   closely with the Governors office to strike a balance between important
   legislative priorities and the reality of fiscal constraints.
   [trans_dot.gif]
