   [trans_dot.gif] Common Sense School Fire Safety Bill Signed Into Law
   [trans_dot.gif]
   Students, teachers, and administrators will be better protected from
   school fires thanks to legislation authored by Senator Jack OConnell
   (D- San Luis Obispo). Senate Bill 575 will require new schools to have
   automatic fire detection systems and will require school modernization
   projects at existing schools to include an automatic fire alarm.
   Schools will also be required to practice fire safety drills more
   frequently to ensure fire readiness. Elementary schools will be
   required to conduct fire drills once a month, and intermediate and high
   schools shall conduct fire drills twice every school year.
   [trans_dot.gif]
   Go
